# Node mock-server engineering standards — {{WORKSPACE_NAME}}

> **Purpose**: The authoritative engineering-conventions document for the mock-server repo(s) in this workspace. Route structure, spec-driven response shapes, seed data, ergonomics — **how we write mock endpoints here**.
> **Last Updated**: {{DATE}}
> **Bootstrapped by**: PipeCrew `/discover` — Phase B2.5.

The mock server mirrors one or more real backend services so frontend developers can run the UI without the full backend stack. Every mock response must match the live OpenAPI spec shape exactly — shape drift here produces UI bugs that look like frontend bugs.

**Stable section anchors (§1–§6) are cited by number from implementer and reviewer agents.** Do not renumber existing sections; you may add §7+.

